Two people were killed in a road accident in the west of Pretoria on Sunday.Best Care ambulance services spokesperson Xander Loubser said this happened on the corner of Quagga Road and Maunde Street around 01:00, Rekord Centurion reported.Loubser said a driver apparently lost control over his vehicle, which overturned and crashed into a pole. When we arrived, a young woman had already died on the scene and two other people were trapped in the vehicle, Loubser said one of the men in the vehicle died after he was taken away from the scene.Mechanical equipment had to be used to remove people from the wreck.In another accident, Best Care treated two seriously injured people on the scene before taking them to Kalafong hospital.Read original story on rekordcenturion.co.za